The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Calcutta, March 6: Corus shareholders will decide on the Tata offer for the AngloDutch steelmaker tomorrow. A court appointed meeting of the shareholders and the extraordinary general meeting (EGM) is lined up in London local time 10 am onwards. The results of the Tata offer of 608 pence a share will be known by afternoon. If approved, Corus shares will be delisted from the London Stock Exchange.

 Mumbai, March 6: The Hindujas claimed that the deal for acquiring 67 per cent stake in Hutchison-Essar is not yet complete and it was still in the race to acquire the mobile operator.

 New Delhi, March 6: Indias crude oil imports have jumped 14 per cent to 90.68 million tonnes (mt) this fiscal as domestic demand for petroleum products increased 5.3 per cent.

 New Delhi, March 6: Bharti Airtel said there was no government scrutiny on the companys decision to buy back 5.6 per cent stake from Vodafone and the transaction was within the foreign investment norms.

 New Delhi, March 6: The government has decided to postpone changes in fdi norms by about a month. The annual review in the foreign direct investment (FDI) policy was due this month but it has been postponed since Parliament is in session.




